## **Setup Instructions**

### Prerequisites
- **Node.js** v18+  
- **npm** package manager  

### 1. Server Setup
```bash
cd server
npm install
npm run dev

Server will run on http://localhost:5000 by default.

API Endpoints:

GET /api/messages – Retrieves chat messages

GET /api/users – Retrieves current online users

GET / – Server health check

2. Client Setup
cd client
npm install
npm run dev


Open http://localhost:5173 in your browser.

Vite will automatically hot reload on file changes.

3. Environment Variables

Server (server/.env):

PORT=5000
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:5173


Client (client/.env):

VITE_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:5000

Usage Instructions

Open the client URL in a browser.

Enter a username and click Join Chat.

Chat with all users in the global room.

Observe typing indicators when users are composing messages.

Click on a user (UI can be extended) to send a private message.

When users join or leave, system notifications are shown.

